Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @Ciabatta{1} and lay onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over half the garlic and drizzle with the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Set aside for now.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the ravioli.

While the water boils, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{120%grams} to the pan and stir-fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @Spinach and Ricotta Ravioli{250%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the mushrooms have browned, reduce the heat and add the remaining garlic. Stir-fry for a further ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Water{100%milliliters} for the sauce and @Wild Mushroom Paste{15%grams}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until the liquid has reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grill your garlic ciabatta until golden, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}.

Warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Add a splash of water to loosen if needed.

Stir through the @Truffle Zest{1%sachet} and season with salt and pepper.

Share the cooked ravioli between your #bowls{} and spoon over the truffle mushroom sauce. Sprinkle over the @Walnuts{20%grams}.

Cut the garlic bread in half diagonally and serve on the side along with the @Wild Rocket{40%grams}.

Drizzle some @olive oil{} and the @Balsamic Glaze{12%milliliters} over the rocket to finish.

Enjoy!